This week Diabetes Australia in conjunction with state and territory
organisations have launched a new campaign 'The Diabetes Low Down' to raise
awareness of how ‘hypos’ affect people living with type 1 and type 2 diabetes
Called the **Diabetes Lowdown** , the campaign aims to change perceptions of
‘hypos' - helping people in the community to better understand them and
letting those who live with them know they're not alone. ****
To help us get the word out there we're asking people to share their hypo
story on Facebook, Instagram or Twitter via video or photograph holding up a
sign describing their hypo feelings #thelowdown2019. All the posts will be
Everyone who creates a video post will go into a draw to win one of five $100
Mastercard vouchers. Check out the conversation and posts so far .
Help us open the discussion about hypos by sharing your story and experience
